author: Kathy Chu
title: Why the TPP Trade Deal Isn’t All Good for Vietnam’s Factories
text:
The landmark 12-country Trans-Pacific Partnership trade deal could bring more business to Vietnamese manufacturers, but there is a potential downside: higher labor costs and strained production at the country’s factories.
Over the past decade, manufacturing labor costs in Vietnam have more than tripled to $1.96 an hour, including benefits, although costs are still much less than China’s $3.27 an hour and the U.S.’s $37.96 an hour,...
